data.meta_description: On December 15, 1960 Fabiola of Aragon married Baudouin, King of the Belgians. At the wedding in the Church of Our Lady of Laeken, she wore a 1926 Art Deco tiara that had been a gift of the Belgian state to her husband's mother, Astrid of Sweden, upon her marriage to Leopold III. Her gown was a masterpiece created by Spanish design legend Cristobal Balenciaga. Peau satin with a mink collar and twenty foot train. His creations were considered the optimal of haute couture in the 1950's and 1960's.
